Privacy Notice
Thank you for using SendBird!
Last Updated: June 22, 2022
SendBird, Inc. and our wholly owned subsidiary SendBird Korea, Inc. (“SendBird”) is committed to respecting the privacy rights of its customers, visitors and other users of its services. We know that you care about how your Personal Information is used and shared, and therefore we take your privacy seriously. You have control over what information you share and whom you share it with. We do not share your Personal Information with people or services without your permission. We will work hard to be a responsible steward of the information we hold. Please read the following to learn more about our privacy practices (“Privacy Policy”).
By using the services provided by SendBird, any other related services, or using the SendBird Website at
www.SendBird.com
(collectively, the “Services”), you accept the practices outlined in this Privacy Policy.
If you do not accept any of the provisions of this Privacy Policy, please do not use the Services.
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact us at
privacy@sendbird.com
or by writing us at: SendBird (ATTN: Privacy), 400 1st Ave. San Mateo, CA 94401, United States.
If you have any questions or security reports, please contact us at
security@sendbird.com
SendBird utilizes valid data transfers mechanisms such as the Standard Contractual Clauses for cross-border data transfers where we deem appropriate.
